From: Xuewen Wang <wangxuewen@kylinos.cn>
Date: Tue, 14 Jul 2026 15:53:58 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] mm/damon: remove trailing semicolons after function
 definitions

Three function definitions terminate with '};' instead of '}',
which is unnecessary and inconsistent with kernel coding style:

- damon_pa_initcall() in paddr.c
- damon_va_initcall() in vaddr.c
- damos_get_some_mem_psi_total() in core.c

No functional change intended.

Link: https://lore.kernel.org/20260714075358.1592393-1-wangxuewen@kylinos.cn
Signed-off-by: Xuewen Wang <wangxuewen@kylinos.cn>
Reviewed-by: SJ Park <sj@kernel.org>
Signed-off-by: SJ Park <sj@kernel.org>
---
 mm/damon/core.c  | 2 +-
 mm/damon/paddr.c | 2 +-
 mm/damon/vaddr.c | 2 +-
 3 files changed, 3 insertions(+), 3 deletions(-)

diff --git a/mm/damon/core.c b/mm/damon/core.c
index 8886a88baa742..6ca84e7af2aa9 100644
--- a/mm/damon/core.c
+++ b/mm/damon/core.c
@@ -3129,7 +3129,7 @@ static u64 damos_get_some_mem_psi_total(void)
 static inline u64 damos_get_some_mem_psi_total(void)
 {
 	return 0;
-};
+}
 
 #endif	/* CONFIG_PSI */
 
diff --git a/mm/damon/paddr.c b/mm/damon/paddr.c
index 547f408304f87..74bd653949385 100644
--- a/mm/damon/paddr.c
+++ b/mm/damon/paddr.c
@@ -646,6 +646,6 @@ static int __init damon_pa_initcall(void)
 	};
 
 	return damon_register_ops(&ops);
-};
+}
 
 subsys_initcall(damon_pa_initcall);
diff --git a/mm/damon/vaddr.c b/mm/damon/vaddr.c
index 011a64bb566b2..5ccf70dc8a30b 100644
--- a/mm/damon/vaddr.c
+++ b/mm/damon/vaddr.c
@@ -950,7 +950,7 @@ static int __init damon_va_initcall(void)
 	if (err)
 		return err;
 	return damon_register_ops(&ops_fvaddr);
-};
+}
 
 subsys_initcall(damon_va_initcall);
 
-- 
2.47.3

